{
  "stem": "1282.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I'm sure you've noticed already from history that he has-- when he came to Budapest, the first thing he did is there were some wealthy Jews that donated a lot of money for him and their homes.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Not their homes, their houses.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were sort of courtyards, and some consisted of 30, 40 apartments.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were large hotel buildings where Jews were beginning to move in to ghetto and they were empty, so Raoul Wallenberg bought them from the German government for very little.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he put up the Swedish flag, and he housed these people in there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Well, it was one thing to get them in there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But to get them out there and to be able to get them out of the country, that was difficult.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Raoul Wallenberg himself couldn't deliver all Schutz-Pass or the-- or the passports himself.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So he used people like us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We not only duplicated many of them, but we also delivered this during the night.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And most of my-- most of the time, we used the sewer system at night.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Because every-- in those countries, in Poland, they have the courtyard and then they've got this huge sewer outlet in the center of the courtyard.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We got into the sewer system, and I knew my way how to get into the courtyard.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And once I got there, I brought food and passports and whatnot.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then we were able to legitimately get them into another group that has snuck them through the border into Romania and, again, try to get them.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "What happened to many of them, we don't know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But the idea was to get them out of Budapest.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Mostly, mostly the Polish younger people that have escaped.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
